===2020 census===
As of the [[2020 United States census|2020 census]], Hutchins had a population of 22 people, with 3 households and 0 families residing in the community. The [[population density]] was 72.8 inhabitants per square mile (28.1/km<sup>2</sup>). There were 11 housing units at an average density of 36.4 per square mile (14.1/km<sup>2</sup>).<ref name="Census2020DP">{{cite web|title=2020 Decennial Census Demographic Profile (DP1)|url=https://api.census.gov/data/2020/dec/dp?get=NAME,DP1_0021P,DP1_0024P,DP1_0025C,DP1_0049C,DP1_0045C,DP1_0069C,DP1_0073C,DP1_0125P,DP1_0126P,DP1_0129P,DP1_0133P,DP1_0137P,DP1_0138P,DP1_0139P,DP1_0141P,DP1_0142P,DP1_0143P,DP1_0145P,DP1_0146P,DP1_0147C,DP1_0148C,DP1_0149C,DP1_0156C,DP1_0157C,DP1_0158C,DP1_0159P,DP1_0160P&for=place%3A37875&in=state%3A19|website=United States Census Bureau|year=2021|access-date=May 1, 2026|df=mdy}}</ref><ref name="Census2020PL">{{cite web|title=2020 Decennial Census Redistricting Data (Public Law 94-171)|url=https://api.census.gov/data/2020/dec/pl?get=NAME,P1_001N,P1_003N,P1_004N,P1_005N,P1_006N,P1_007N,P1_008N,P1_009N,P2_001N,P2_002N,H1_001N,H1_002N&for=place%3A37875&in=state%3A19|website=United States Census Bureau|year=2021|access-date=May 1, 2026|df=mdy}}</ref>

The median age was 45.0 years. 13.6% of residents were under the age of 18 and 27.3% of residents were 65 years of age or older. 0.0% were between the ages of 20 and 24, 31.8% were from 25 to 44, and 22.7% were from 45 to 64. For every 100 females there were 100.0 males, and for every 100 females age 18 and over there were 72.7 males age 18 and over.<ref name="Census2020DP"/>

All residents lived in rural areas.<ref name="Census2020DHC">{{cite web|title=2020 Decennial Census Demographic and Housing Characteristics (DHC)|url=https://api.census.gov/data/2020/dec/dhc?get=NAME,P2_002N,P2_003N&for=place%3A37875&in=state%3A19|website=United States Census Bureau|year=2023|access-date=May 1, 2026|df=mdy}}</ref>

No households had children under the age of 18. One of the three households had a male householder with no spouse or partner present, and two of the three households had a female householder with no spouse or partner present. All households were non-families and were made up of individuals, and two of the three households had someone living alone who was 65 years of age or older.<ref name="Census2020DP"/>

Of the 11 housing units, 72.7% were vacant. All three occupied housing units were owner-occupied. The homeowner vacancy rate was 25.0% and the rental vacancy rate was 0.0%.<ref name="Census2020DP"/>

